data.description: Under contract-accepting backup offers. WELCOME TO THE GATED COMMUNITY OF HERNANDO OAKS! This home sits on a .31 acre, backing up to conservation, is less that 1 year old with $20,000 of upgrades. They include a black rod iron backyard fence perfect for privacy and pets. Overlooking the backyard is a screened, covered lanai for relaxing, entertaining, or outdoor dining.  The home also has a screened front entrance. Other upgrades include ceiling fans, ADT security system and additional recessed lighting. The home is concrete block constructed, one-story layout optimizes living space with an open concept kitchen overlooking the living area and dining room. The well-appointed kitchen comes with built-in dishwasher, electric range, pantry and microwave. The master bedroom is roomy and has a master bath with double sinks, a walk in shower, a huge walk in closet . Two additional bedrooms share the second bathroom. The third bedroom or home office,  is located near the laundry room, which includes the washer and dryer.  Hernando Oaks is a golf cart friendly community with a beautifully designed 18 hole course and its own restaurant. Hernando Oaks is minutes from shopping, restaurants, banks, and medical facilities. It is conveniently located off US 41 and close to the Suncoast Parkway and I75.  Just 1 hr-Tampa Intl Airport; 2 hrs-Orlando theme Parks; 1.5-2 hrs-St Pete & Clearwater Beaches; 30 min-Weeki Wachee Springs (kayaking, canoeing, fishing, Mermaid Show, Water Park).
